30/07/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Albania and Montenegro have reached an agreement to step up joint efforts against organised crime. During a meeting Thursday (29 July), Montenegrin Interior Minister Dragan Djurovic and Albanian Police Minister Igli Toska agreed to beef up border security to curb human trafficking and drug smuggling. "We have identified all the drug smuggling and human trafficking networks and hope that our collaboration will soon bring concrete results," Toska said. (B92, Mina - 29/07/04)
